{"title":"Apple Weekly Update: HomePod and iMac Pro discontinued, but new devices may be on the way","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/3611335/apple-weekly-update-imac-pro-homepod-discontinued-spring-event-ios-macos-updates.html#tk.rss_all","date":1615717800000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><section role=\"main\" id=\"page-wrapper\"><article itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/NewsArticle\"><meta itemprop=\"keywords\" content=\"apple,  \"><header><ins data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-4268075595326305\" data-ad-slot=\"9945794902\" data-ad-format=\"link\" data-adsbygoogle-status=\"done\"><ins id=\"aswift_0_expand\" tabindex=\"0\" title=\"Advertisement\" aria-label=\"Advertisement\"><ins id=\"aswift_0_anchor\"></ins></ins></ins><section><h3 itemprop=\"description\">Everything you missed from the past week.</h3></section><div><p>Executive Editor, <span itemprop=\"publisher\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Organization\"><span itemprop=\"name\">Macworld</span><meta itemprop=\"url\" content=\"https://www.macworld.com\"><meta itemprop=\"logo\" content=\"https://alt.idgesg.net/images/furniture/macworld/MW_logo_300x300.png\"></span><span>|</span> <span itemprop=\"datePublished\" content=\"2021-03-14T03:30-0700\"><span>Mar 14, 2021 3:30 am PDT</span></span></p></div></header><div><div><figure itemprop=\"image\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"><meta itemprop=\"representativeOfPage\" content=\"1\"><meta itemprop=\"height\" content=\"675\"><meta itemprop=\"width\" content=\"1200\"><meta itemprop=\"url\" content=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/03/weekly-apple-update-314-100880655-large.jpg\"><img data-original=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/03/weekly-apple-update-314-100880655-large.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"weekly apple update 314\" itemprop=\"contentUrl\" src=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/03/weekly-apple-update-314-100880655-large.jpg\"><figcaption kioskedhash_production=\"11429_e09d949c66882321cb634a8d45c6bde1\" data-kiosked-context-name=\"kskdUIContext_01f0r569n5dev0kxbmbgayqx09\"><span itemprop=\"copyrightHolder\">IDG</span></figcaption></figure></div></div><section><div id=\"drr-container\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"><p>While we here at Macworld read and write about Apple all week long, we totally get that you might not. But since you’re here now, allow us to catch you up on all of the stuff you need to know from the past week.</p><h2>HomePod plays its last notes</h2><p>To cap the week, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.co.uk/news/apple-kills-homepod-shift-focus-mini-3802669/\">Apple pulled the plug on its original HomePod smart speaker</a>, with the Space Gray model already sold out and gone forever. Apple’s $299 smart speaker never quite took off, but Apple isn’t giving up on its home audio ambitions—the mini will stick around and <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3611668/homepod-mini-succeed-u1-ultra-wideband-price-features-size-sound.html\">might just succeed where its older sibling failed</a>.</p><h2>iMac Pro gets the ax</h2><p>While <a href=\"https://www.macworld.co.uk/news/new-imac-3696859/\">rumors swirl about a new M1-based redesign</a> in the works, Apple is trimming the iMac herd. While you can still technically buy one, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3610715/apple-discontinues-imac-pro-as-signs-point-to-imminent-m1-launch.html\">Apple has decided to discontinue the high-end iMac Pro</a>, and it’s unlikely that there will be an M1 replacement. Karen Haslam at Macworld UK <a href=\"https://www.macworld.co.uk/news/doesnt-matter-discontinued-imac-pro-3802473/\">doesn't think it really matters</a>, while <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3610787/the-imac-pro-was-the-ultimate-intel-mac-of-its-era.html\">Jason Snell wrote a eulogy</a> for what was once the fastest Mac ever made.</p><h2>Circle March 23 on your calendar</h2><p>We’re anxiously awaiting an invitation to an Apple event this month that will hopefully bring new <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3434061/ipad-2020-rumors-everything-you-need-to-know.html\">iPads</a>, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.co.uk/news/new-airpods-2020-3780443/\">AirPods</a>, and the long-awaited <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3536073/apple-airtags-bluetooth-track-find-my-ultrawide-band-u1-keychain-locate-lost-items.html\">AirTags</a>, The latest rumor has <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3252331/apples-event-calendar-when-is-the-next-apple-event.html\">targeted Tuesday, March 23</a> as the possible date of the event, so if you have any plans for that day at around 10 am PT, we recommend canceling them.</p><div><p><img onclick=\"jwplayer('bottomRightPlayer').remove(); this.style.display = 'none';\" id=\"jw-standalone-close-button\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><div id=\"bottomRightPlayer\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-label=\"Video Player\" role=\"application\" aria-describedby=\"jw-shortcuts-tooltip-explanation\"><div dir=\"auto\"><p>MacBook Buying Guide 2020</p></div><p><span aria-live=\"assertive\"></span><span aria-live=\"assertive\">Volume 0%</span></p></div></div><h2>Important security holes plugged in iOS and macOS</h2><p>It’ll still be another week or two until we get an official release of <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3605528/ios-14-5-features-release-date-beta-how-to-install.html\">iOS 14.5</a> and <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3605988/new-features-in-macos-big-sur-113-safari-customization-options-enhanced-support-for-iphoneipad-apps.html\">Big Sur 11.3</a>, but there are updates out for the <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3610737/apple-pushes-ios-14-4-1-with-important-safari-security-updates.html\">iPad</a>, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3610737/apple-pushes-ios-14-4-1-with-important-safari-security-updates.html\">iPhone</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3610704/macos-big-sur-11-2-3-update-is-now-available-with-webkit-fix.html\">Mac</a> that you should install if you haven’t already. They fix a memory corruption issue that may lead to arbitrary code execution, which is something you never actually want to happen.</p><div><p>Note: When you purchase something after clicking links in our articles, we may earn a small commission. Read our <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/about/affiliates.html\">affiliate link policy</a> for more details.</p></div></div><div><p>Michael Simon covers all things iPhone, iPad, Mac, and Apple Watch, with a little Android thrown in. You can usually find him with his nose buried in a screen. The best way to yell at him is on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/morlium?lang=en\">Twitter</a>.</p></div></section></article></section></div>","author":"Michael Simon","siteTitle":"Macworld","siteHash":"37e84dd5a21fa961d6d6630e269546024dbb7741b2e2fadbe74f47383c70dfbb","entryHash":"fd275e3c17de8d269a3cc846dfbceb4d33f2a4c279a65cacb8e7eac44a660cd2","category":"Apple"}